   SUPERFUND ENFORCEMENT CHIEF is to join law firm.
   Lloyd Guerci will leave the Environmental Protection
Agency next week to become a partner in the Washington office
of the Chicago law firm Mayer, Brown &amp; Platt. Mr. Guerci, who
as a career civil servant has extensive experience in toxic
and hazardous waste regulation, said he chose Mayer Brown
because of its environmental practice, which he hopes to
expand.
   Mr. Guerci said that his work at the 45-lawyer Washington
office will include representing businesses before the EPA on
pollution-enforcement matters. Currently, federal law permits
an official to lobby his former agency immediately after his
departure provided the lobbying does not involve matters in
which he was personally and substantially involved, and
provided the official's staff was not involved in the matter
during his last year on the job.
   Tougher restrictions go into effect Jan. 1.
